==English==

===Pronunciation===
* [[IPA]] US [ˈhoʊmi]

===Etymology===
Shortened form of [[homeboy]].

===Noun===
'''homey''', plural '''homeys'''

#A term used to refer informally to another's friends. <br> Example: ''Hey there, Alex, my '''homey'''''!
#Someone, particularly a male acquaintance, from one's hometown.
#A close friend or fellow member of a youth gang.
#An inner-city youth.

===Usage note===
Very informal slang associated with urban [[w:African-American Vernacular English]].
